# :material-frequently-asked-questions: FAQ & Troubleshooting

Find quick answers to common questions about Hardware, Software, and Ordering.

!!! tip "Can't find your answer?"
    Use the **Search Bar** at the top of the page, or check our [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/VIEWESMART/VIEWE-FAQ/issues) for community solutions.

<br>

--

## 💻 Software Development (ESP32)

??? question "Which library should I use: LVGL or Arduino_GFX?"
    * **Arduino_GFX**: Best for simple drawing (circles, lines, text) and raw driver performance. It is the underlying driver for LVGL.
    * **LVGL**: Best for complex UI (Buttons, Sliders, Charts, Animations). We recommend using **LVGL** for professional products.

??? question "Do you support MicroPython or CircuitPython?"
    Yes, the hardware supports it, but our official tutorials focus on **C++ (Arduino/ESP-IDF)**.
    Community members have successfully ported MicroPython drivers for ST7701/ST7789 screens used in our modules.

??? question "How to use the onboard SD Card?"
    The SD card slot typically uses the **SPI** or **SDMMC** interface.
    * For ESP32-S3, we recommend **SDMMC** (1-bit or 4-bit) for faster speed.
    * Refer to the [SD Card Tutorial](../software/tutorials/topics/sd-card.md) for pin definitions and sample code.

<br>
## 💻 Software Development

We provide comprehensive support for the most popular development frameworks to help you get your display project running quickly.

-----

### 📦 Development Frameworks

### 🔹 Arduino

The most popular framework for rapid prototyping and access to a vast ecosystem of libraries.

  * **Library Support**: Fully compatible with the `ESP32_Display_Panel` library, which can be installed via the Arduino Library Manager or manually as a `.zip` file.
  * **Easy Configuration**: Supports simple LVGL integration by placing the `lv_conf.h` file in your project or library directory.
  * **Optimization**: Includes specific configurations for ESP32-S3 RGB LCDs, such as **Bounce Buffer** settings to prevent screen drift.
    👉 [**Arduino Development Guide**](https://www.google.com/search?q=../software/arduino/index.md)

### 🔹 ESP-IDF

Espressif's native development framework, designed for professional-grade applications and maximum performance.

  * **SDK Integration**: The SDK for `arduino-esp32 v3.x.x` is located in the `tools/esp32-arduino-libs/idf-release_x` directory of the installation path.
  * **Advanced Control**: Recommended for projects requiring precise task scheduling, such as pinning RGB initialization and LVGL handlers to the same CPU core.
    👉 [**ESP-IDF Development Guide**](https://www.google.com/search?q=../software/esp-idf/index.md)

### 🔹 PlatformIO

A powerful, professional environment for embedded development with advanced project management features.

  * **Project Templates**: Use our provided PlatformIO examples to jumpstart development for **ESP32-S3-LCD-EV-Board** series.
  * **Custom Boards**: Easily adapt to custom hardware by modifying the `boards/ESP-LCD.json` configuration file.
    👉 [**PlatformIO Development Guide**](https://www.google.com/search?q=../software/platformio/index.md)

-----

### ❓ Common Questions

??? question "Which library should I use: LVGL or Arduino\_GFX?"
\* **Arduino\_GFX**: Best for simple drawing tasks (circles, lines, text) and raw driver performance. It often serves as the underlying driver for higher-level UI libraries.
\* **LVGL**: The industry standard for complex UIs featuring buttons, sliders, charts, and smooth animations. We highly recommend **LVGL** for professional product development.

??? question "Do you support MicroPython or CircuitPython?"
Yes, our hardware is fully compatible. While our official documentation focuses on **C++ (Arduino/ESP-IDF)**, community members have successfully ported drivers for the ST7701 and ST7789 screens used in our modules.

??? question "How to use the onboard SD Card?"
The SD card slot typically operates via **SPI** or **SDMMC** interfaces.
\* For the **ESP32-S3**, we recommend using **SDMMC** (1-bit or 4-bit mode) to achieve significantly faster data transfer speeds.
\* Detailed pin definitions and sample code can be found in our [SD Card Tutorial](https://www.google.com/search?q=../software/tutorials/topics/sd-card.md).


